  "prompt": "What are the best recipes for small batch chocolate chip cookies?",
  "response": "Here are a couple of the best recipes for small-batch chocolate chip cookies. These recipes are perfect for when you want a quick, satisfying treat without making a large quantity:\n\n### Small-Batch Chocolate Chip Cookies\n\n#### Recipe 1: Classic Small-Batch Chocolate Chip Cookies\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 tablespoons unsalted butter, softened\n- 3 tablespoons granulated sugar\n- 3 tablespoons brown sugar, packed\n- 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1 egg yolk\n- 1/2 cup all-purpose flour\n- 1/8 teaspoon baking soda\n- 1/8 teaspoon salt\n- 1/3 cup chocolate chips\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Preheat your oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\n2. In a small bowl, use a hand mixer or whisk to cream together the softened butter, granulated sugar, and brown sugar until smooth and creamy.\n3. Mix in the vanilla extract and egg yolk until well combined.\n4. In another bowl, whisk together the flour, baking soda, and salt, then gradually add this to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined.\n5. Fold in the chocolate chips.\n6. Scoop the dough onto the prepared baking sheet, spacing them about 2 inches apart. You should be able to make around 6 cookies.\n7. Bake for 9-11 minutes, or until the edges are golden brown and the centers have just set.\n8. Allow the cookies to cool on the baking sheet for a few minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely.\n\n#### Recipe 2: One-Pan Small-Batch Skillet Cookie\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 2 tablespoons unsalted butter\n- 2 tablespoons granulated sugar\n- 2 tablespoons brown sugar, packed\n- 1/4 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- Pinch of salt\n- 1 egg yolk\n- 6 tablespoons all-purpose flour\n- 1/8 teaspoon baking soda\n- 1/4 cup chocolate chips\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Preheat the oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C).\n2. In a small, oven-safe skillet, melt the butter over low heat. Remove from heat and add the granulated sugar, brown sugar, vanilla extract, and salt, stirring until well combined.\n3. Let the mixture cool slightly, then stir in the egg yolk.\n4. Add the flour and baking soda to the skillet, stirring until just combined. Make sure the batter is even in the skillet, and then sprinkle the chocolate chips on top.\n5. Place the skillet in the preheated oven and bake for 12-15 minutes, or until the edges are golden brown and the center is just set.\n6. Allow to cool slightly before serving directly from the skillet for a gooey, delicious treat.\n\nThese recipes will give you fresh, warm chocolate chip cookies right out of the oven and are perfect for satisfying a cookie craving without a lot of leftovers. Enjoy!",
